{% set currentBooks = readingList | activeBook %} {% set latestPost =
collections.posts | reverse | first %} {% set previousEvent = collections.events
| pastFromCollection | last %} {% set nextEvent = collections.events |
futureFromCollection | first %} {% if previousEvent == nextEvent %} {% set
nextEvent = false %} {% endif %}

<h1>Now</h1>
<p>
  Rather than an about page… this is a list of things that are going on
  <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener">now</a>.
</p>

<ul class="nowList">
  <li>
    <strong>Location</strong>
    <div>
      Since 2014 I've been living in
      <span itemprop="text"
        ><a href="{{ now.location.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >{{ now.location.name }}, UK</a
        ></span
      >. And for the immediate future I don't see myself leaving anytime soon.
    </div>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Employment</strong>
    <div>
      I'm currently a {{ now.employment[0].role }} for
      <img
        src="https://v1.indieweb-avatar.11ty.dev/{{ now.employment[0].url | urlencode }}/"
        alt="{{ now.employment[0].name }} logo"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="34"
        height="34"
        class="nowList__album"
      />
      <strong
        ><a href="{{ now.employment[0].url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >{{ now.employment[0].name }}</a
        ></strong
      >. You can see a full employment history on my
      <a href="/resume">resume</a>.
    </div>
  </li>

  {#
  <li>
    Current toolbox:<br />
    {% for tool in now.toolbox %}
    <a href="{{ tool.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{{ tool.name }}</a
    >{% if loop.last != true %}, {% endif %} {% endfor %}
  </li>
  #}

  <li>
    <strong>Blogging</strong>
    <div>
      I used to write blog posts semi-regularly… now not so much! Most recently
      I wrote
      <strong
        ><a href="{{ latestPost.url }}">{{ latestPost.data.title }}</a></strong
      >. You can <a href="/blog">view a list of all blog posts here</a>.
    </div>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Albums this month</strong>
    <div>This month I've been enjoying:</div>

    <ul class="nowList__list">
      {% for album in lastfm %}
      <li>
        <img
          src="{{ album.image[0]['#text'] }}"
          alt="{{ album.name }} Cover"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          width="34"
          height="34"
        />
        <span
          ><a href="{{ album.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
            ><strong>{{ album.name }}</strong></a
          >
          by <em>{{ album.artist.name }}</em></span
        >
      </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>

    <p>
      <span class="js-nowPlaying"></span>

      My music listening gets logged to
      <a href="https://last.fm/user/jamesdoc">Last.fm</a> by
      <a href="/blog/2022/sleeve">Sleeve</a>.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Reading list</strong>
    <div>
      {% if currentBooks.length > 0 %} Right now I'm reading {% for book in
      currentBooks %}
      <strong>{{ book.name }}</strong> by
      <em>{{ book.additional.author }}</em>{% if loop.last != true %},{% else
      %}.{% endif %} {% endfor %} {% else %} {% set b = readingList | sort(true,
      true, 'epoch') | first %} {% set cover = b.cover.scaled | last %} I've
      just finished reading <strong>{{ b.name }}</strong> by {{
      b.additional.author }}. {% endif %} I keep track of all the books I'm
      reading through a big reading list in Trello and then pull them into this
      site. You can <a href="/reading-list">view the full reading list</a>.
    </div>
  </li>

    <li>
    <strong>Recently on the internet</strong>
    <div>
      I keep track of articles and blogposts I'm reading (or want to get around
      to reading) in
      <a href="https://instapaper.com/p/jamesdoc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instapaper</a
      >. Here are five articles that I've enjoyed recently:
    </div>

    <ul class="nowList__list">
      {% for article in instapaper %} {% if (loop.index <= 5) %}
      <li>
        <img
          src="https://v1.indieweb-avatar.11ty.dev/{{ article.url | urlencode }}/"
          alt=""
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          width="34"
          height="34"
        />
        <span
          ><a href="{{ article.url }}" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
            {{ article.title }}</a
          >.<br />
          Read on {{ article.time | readableDate }}.</span
        >
      </li>
      {% endif %} {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Events in the diary</strong>
    <div>
      The last event I was at was
      <img
        src="https://v1.indieweb-avatar.11ty.dev/{{ previousEvent.data.externalUrl | urlencode }}/"
        alt="{{ previousEvent.data.title }} logo"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="34"
        height="34"
        class="nowList__album"
      />
      <strong
        ><a
          href="{{ previousEvent.data.externalUrl }}"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          >{{ previousEvent.data.organiser }} – {{ previousEvent.data.title
          }}</a
        ></strong
      >
      on {{ previousEvent.data.date | readableDate }} ({{
      previousEvent.data.role }}). {% if nextEvent %} Next up is
      <img
        src="https://v1.indieweb-avatar.11ty.dev/{{ nextEvent.data.externalUrl | urlencode }}/"
        alt="{{ nextEvent.data.title }} logo"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="34"
        height="34"
        class="nowList__album"
      />
      <strong
        ><a
          href="{{ nextEvent.data.externalUrl }}"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          >{{ nextEvent.data.title }}</a
        ></strong
      >
      on {{ nextEvent.data.date | readableDate }} in {{
      nextEvent.data.location.city }} ({{ nextEvent.data.role }}). {% endif %}
      <a href="/events">View the full list</a>.
    </div>
  </li>
</ul>

